TopicTitle: Does anyone have a list of proposed and canceled rockets?

Articles.Content:
Like the title says, I'm looking for a list of proposed and canceled rockets.

I've did a few Google searches but it came up with no actual results, maybe I'm not using the right words.

Any particular kinds of rockets? There were many different proposals for getting to the Moon in the Apollo period, all based on either Moon or Earth Rendezvous. And then there were the post moon-landing Apollo ideas, not to mention thousands of ideas after that and from other countries

Short answer, yes, this: http://www.astronautix.com/lvs/index.htm

Really though, just the ones that have flown, let alone proposals that never made it, is going to be a huge list. That link is launch vehicles only, and the list for spacecraft is just as long. Astronautix is your best place to start, it's kind-of the encyclopedia of rockets, but I'd suggest narrowing down your search to be a bit more specific, as there is a lot of stuff out there.

PS: Here is a nice picture of most of the rockets that have been flown to date. http://i.imgur.com/7yHH0TV.jpg
